# Executable-script line endings are load-bearing, not cosmetic:
# bin/harness is a bash script — Git Bash on Windows tolerates CRLF
# (igncr), but a stock Linux bash does not, so a working tree that ever
# crosses from a Windows checkout to a Linux host (zip, docker volume,
# network share) must carry LF. bin/harness.cmd is the inverse: cmd.exe
# parsing has known CRLF-only edge cases (multi-line blocks, goto).
bin/harness text eol=lf
bin/harness.cmd text eol=crlf
